        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I've created a form using the following code to add an input element:\r\n\r\n{code:title=Form|borderStyle=solid}\r\n$Element = new Zend_Form_Element_Text('field');\r\n$Element->setRequired();\r\n$Element->addValidators(array(\r\n    new Zend_Validate_Regex('\/^[[:alpha:]\\']+$\/iu'),\r\n    new Zend_Validate_StringLength(array('min' => 3, 'max' => 50))));\r\n$Element->addFilters(array(new Zend_Filter_StringTrim()));\r\n$this->addElement($Element);\r\nunset($Element);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis is a summary of what I input in the field, what I should got and what I *really* got.\r\n||Input||Expected||Gotten||\r\n|test|true|true|\r\n|test99|false|false|\r\n|\u00f2\u00e8\u00f9test\u00f2\u00f2|true|true|\r\n|test\u00e0|true|\"There was an internal error while using the pattern '\/^[[:alpha:]\\']+$\/iu'\"|\r\n|te\u00e0\u00e0st|true|true|\r\n|\u00e0\u00e0\u00f2\u00f2\u00ec\u00f9\u00e9\u00e9|true|true|\r\n|\u00e8\u00f9\u00f2\u00eciiee\u00e0|true|\"There was an internal error while using the pattern '\/^[[:alpha:]\\']+$\/iu'\"|\r\n\r\nMoreover, if I try to run the input in a normal preg_match, I got the expected results as shown in the following table:\r\n||Input||Expected||Gotten||\r\n|test|true|true|\r\n|test99|false|false|\r\n|\u00f2\u00e8\u00f9test\u00f2\u00f2|true|true|\r\n|test\u00e0|true|true|\r\n|te\u00e0\u00e0st|true|true|\r\n|\u00e0\u00e0\u00f2\u00f2\u00ec\u00f9\u00e9\u00e9|true|true|\r\n|\u00e8\u00f9\u00f2\u00eciiee\u00e0|true|true|\r\n\r\nAs you can see, the validator seems to fail when the '\u00e0' is at the end of the string. The same weird behavior can be seen using the Zend_Validate_Alpha too. In this case, sometimes, the view shows an empty error string. I mean that it will show the list tag (li) as he wants to show an error, but this one is empty.\r\n\r\nNote: I found that the problem is exactly in this method of the Zend_Filter_StringTrim\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_Filter_StringTrim|borderStyle=solid}\r\n    protected function _unicodeTrim($value, $charlist = '\\\\\\\\s')\r\n    { \/\/ here the value it's ok\r\n        $chars = preg_replace(\r\n            array( '\/[\\^\\-\\]\\\\\\]\/S', '\/\\\\\\{4}\/S', '\/\\\/\/'),\r\n            array( '\\\\\\\\\\\\0', '\\\\', '\\\/' ),\r\n            $charlist\r\n        );\r\n\r\n        $pattern = '^[' . $chars . ']*|[' . $chars . ']*$';\r\n        return preg_replace(\"\/$pattern\/sSD\", '', $value);  \/\/ here the last \u00e0 (a multibyte char) has been truncated\r\n    }\r\n{code}"
        },
